---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Widget embed"
  description="How to embed the feedbackmonk widget on your site. Anonymous-by-default, optional JWT, zero third-party fetches."
>
  <header class="page-header">
    <h1>Widget embed</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      The widget is a 17&nbsp;KB ES module. You drop one
      <code>&lt;script&gt;</code> tag on your page; it mounts a launcher
      button in the bottom-right corner and submits feedback over your own
      domain &mdash; not via a tracker.
    </p>
  </header>

  <section aria-labelledby="quickstart-heading">
    <h2 id="quickstart-heading">Quickstart</h2>
    <p>
      Add the script tag. Replace <code>YOUR_PROJECT_ID</code> with the
      project UUID from <code>/admin/projects</code>.
    </p>
    <pre><code>{`<script
  type="module"
  src="https://cdn.feedbackmonk.com/widget.js"
  data-project-id="YOUR_PROJECT_ID"
></script>`}</code></pre>
    <p>
      That's it. The launcher auto-mounts on
      <code>DOMContentLoaded</code>. Add <code>data-fbm-no-auto-mount</code>
      if you'd rather call <code>mountFeedbackMonk()</code> manually.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section aria-labelledby="identity-heading">
    <h2 id="identity-heading">Identity modes</h2>
    <h3>Anonymous (default)</h3>
    <p>
      With no <code>data-jwt</code> attribute, the widget submits
      anonymously. A first-party cookie scoped to the API domain
      (<code>X-Feedbackmonk-Anon-Cookie</code>) lets the admin console
      group submissions from the same browser session without ever
      learning who the user is.
    </p>

    <h3>Authenticated (JWT mode)</h3>
    <p>
      If your app already signs a JWT for the user, pass it via
      <code>data-jwt</code>:
    </p>
    <pre><code>{`<script
  type="module"
  src="https://cdn.feedbackmonk.com/widget.js"
  data-project-id="YOUR_PROJECT_ID"
  data-jwt="eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIs..."
></script>`}</code></pre>
    <p>
      feedbackmonk verifies the JWT against the public key you registered
      and attaches the verified claim to the submission. This JWT is the
      only identity feedbackmonk ever stores for an end-user
      (DEC-FBR-04). No callbacks to your auth provider; no long-lived
      bearer token retention.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section aria-labelledby="programmatic-heading">
    <h2 id="programmatic-heading">Programmatic mount</h2>
    <pre><code>{`import { mountFeedbackMonk } from "@feedbackmonk/widget";
await mountFeedbackMonk({
  projectId: "YOUR_PROJECT_ID",
  jwt: optionalJwt,
  apiBase: "https://api.feedbackmonk.com", // optional override
});`}</code></pre>
  </section>

  <section aria-labelledby="config-heading">
    <h2 id="config-heading">Widget config (read-only)</h2>
    <p>
      On mount, the widget fetches
      <code>GET /api/v1/projects/&#123;project_id&#125;/widget-config</code>.
      The response shape (Contract&nbsp;C12) drives the modal's labels and
      visible kinds:
    </p>
    <pre><code>{`{
  "project_id": "...",
  "brand": {
    "name": "Acme",
    "footer_text": "powered by feedbackmonk"
  },
  "auth_modes": ["auth", "anonymous"],
  "submission_kinds": ["bug", "feature", "question", "other"],
  "max_body_chars": 16384
}`}</code></pre>
    <p>
      The <code>brand.footer_text</code> is <code>"powered by feedbackmonk"</code>
      on the Free tier and <code>null</code> on paid tiers (FR-FBR-14).
      That toggle is enforced at the data layer in
      <code>feedbackmonk-core::tier::tier_quotas()</code> &mdash; not at
      render time.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section aria-labelledby="constraints-heading">
    <h2 id="constraints-heading">Constraints</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Bundle size:</strong> ≤ 30,720 bytes total (FR-FBR-04).
        Currently 16,829&nbsp;B &mdash; 45% headroom. Enforced by the
        <em>widget-bundle-size</em> Verification Oracle, Probe&nbsp;A.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Zero third-party tracker hostnames:</strong> the
        <em>widget-bundle-size</em> Oracle Probe&nbsp;B greps every
        <code>dist/*</code> artifact against an 18-hostname allowlist.
        Any drift fails CI.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>CSP-safe:</strong> no <code>unsafe-inline</code> or
        <code>unsafe-eval</code> required. Styles are emitted as a
        sibling <code>.css</code> file; the only inline DOM literal is a
        single static SVG.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>A11y:</strong> <code>role="dialog"</code>,
        <code>aria-modal</code>, full keyboard trap, ESC restores focus,
        visible focus indicators. Verified via Playwright + axe-core in
        every CI run.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section aria-labelledby="versioning-heading">
    <h2 id="versioning-heading">Versioning</h2>
    <p>
      The widget binary is served from
      <code>https://cdn.feedbackmonk.com/widget.js</code> as the rolling
      "current" major version. Wire-shape changes are gated behind a new
      script URL (<code>widget@v2.js</code>); embedders pin if they need
      strict reproducibility.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-header { margin-block: 2rem 1.5rem; }
  pre { max-width: 100%; }
</style>
